<font color="#FF0000">DON'T FORGET YOUR WINGMAN!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct  4 11:13:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Friend Tom:<br>
I don't tolerate you...I accept and respect almost everything you say.<br><br>
I accept war.<br><br>
I don't always accept the motives for going to war or the crimes against people that get caught up in the mechanics of war.  Surely you have observed violations well outside the vague parameters of ethics.  Perhaps there is a difference in murdering and killing... achieving and wasting.. building and destroying.  Listen carefully, Tom... It is your first hand evidence that justifies a valid protest... it is a clarion message of respect for human life.  I join you in your protest.<br><br>
Super Art:<br><br>
Understanding that comes with age and maturity may have helped many in dealing with trauma (17-23) and not have allowed or had such an adverse impact upon ultimate future development.  However, it makes sense to contemplate that more mature young men may have perceived matters in a more serious fashion or brought with them a well developed bag of inviolate rules which were violated.  You are an intelligent and sensitive man.  Perhaps your finer filtering of the event(s) retained more crap than others who lets some stuff slide.<br><br>
Silent Warrior:<br><br>
Sorry, Ozone Breath... but when somebody takes a shot at you, they take a shot at me.  Remember, in your wake of burned hydrocarbons, foul emissions from your malodoreous T-shirt, fetid fragrances of stale beer and rancid Spam.. there is an open cockpit of flapping metal, straining rivets and beating rotor blades occupied by one devoted brother who is struggling to keep up.  (Cookie.. who hitched a ride is wearing his gas mask.  The lens are fogged up from drooling over my four mounted M-60s.)  The SAMs are thick (Spatz's Antagonistic Mumblings) but I am not concerned... he can't shoot any better than Cookie.  Good Grief!  Hope I didn't piss off my Jarhead doorgunner.  Hopefully, he is tuned into Armed Forces Radio on the ADF, listening to old reruns of Dragnet.<br><br>
We're on you tail.. in the same line of fire!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four 
